# Claude Baseline Usage

This file defines the non-interactive Claude command template used by
`baseline/run_pipeline.py`.

## Command template

```bash
claude -p --dangerously-skip-permissions "create a new a.txt"
```

`run_pipeline.py` will parse this command and replace the final quoted prompt
with a generated full prompt (from `baseline/prompt.md` + issue/PR context).

## How to run the baseline pipeline

From any working directory:

```bash
python /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/run_pipeline.py \
  --repos-root /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/repo \
  --result-root /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/output
```

Dry-run mode (fetch + file generation only, no Claude execution):

```bash
python /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/run_pipeline.py \
  --repos-root /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/repo \
  --result-root /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/output \
  --dry-run
```

## Prerequisites

- `gh` installed and authenticated (`gh auth login`).
- `claude` CLI installed and available in `PATH`.
- Environment exports configured in:
  `/home/cc/claude-code-forge/start_claude_code.sh`

## Output layout (per instance)

`baseline/output/<repo>/<issue_number>/` includes:

- `metadata/` (issue, PR, patch, generated prompt)
- `files/` (Docker/test and agent-generated changed files)
- checker-ready files at root:
  - `issue_<n>.json`
  - `claude.dockerfile`
  - `test*.py`
- `bundle/` with the same checker-ready content

## F2P check

```bash
python /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/f2p_from_swegent_bundle.py \
  /home/cc/claude-code-forge/baseline/output/MLE-agent/273
```
